olive oil
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet barbecue seasoning
1 packet sriracha
15 g butter
1 bag slaw mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
2 clove garlic
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut the carrot and beetroot into fries. Place the veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt. Toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the veggie fries are baking, finely chop the garlic. Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves.

When the fries have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the pork mince, breaking it up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the garlic and barbecue seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the sriracha and the butter and toss until combined. Reduce the heat to low, then sprinkle over the shredded Cheddar cheese and cover with a lid (or foil) until melted, 2-3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

In a large bowl, combine the slaw mix, baby spinach, mango mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

Divide the rainbow veggie fries and sriracha BBQ pork between plates. Serve with the mango mayo slaw.